The paper focuses on visual tracking and uses large amounts of unlabeled video to learn models without manual human supervision. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper leverages the natural temporal coherency of color to create a model that learns to colorize gray-scale videos, which involves learning to track visual regions. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also deals with video processing (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) as it discusses the correlation between failures to track and failures to colorize, indicating that advancing video colorization may further improve self-supervised visual tracking.
